<h2>Error</h2>
<p>Sorry there was a problem with submitting the form. Please try again.</p>

<h3>Dev tip!</h3>
<p>This is most likely because of your smtp settings in the web.config file at the root of the site.</p>
<p>It probably looks like this:</p>
<pre>
&lt;system.net&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;mailSettings&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;smtp from=&quot;noreply@example.com&quot;&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;network host=&quot;127.0.0.1&quot; userName=&quot;username&quot; password=&quot;password&quot; /&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/smtp&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;/mailSettings&gt;
&lt;/system.net&gt;
</pre>

<p>You will need to either enter some valid smtp settings for sending emails, or you can use something like <a href="https://smtp4dev.codeplex.com/">smtp4dev</a> which acts like an SMTP server on your machine.</p>
